<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.281376>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Ctenus serratipes (male MPEG 9007 and female MPEG 9008). Male genitalia. A. Male palp, ventral view; B. Male palp, retrolateral view. Scale bar: 2.00 mm. Female genitalia. C. Epigynum, ventral view; D. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale bar: 0.50 mm. Abbreviations: C, conductor; CD, copulatory ducts; CY, cymbium; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LBP, laminar basal projection of the embolus; LL, lateral lobes; LS, lateral sectors; MA, median apophysis; MS, median sector; OL, ovoid lobes; TE, tegulum; TI, tibia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/281376/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.281377>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Ctenus serratipes (MPEG 9007), left metatarsus IV. A. dorsal view; B. retrolateral view; C. prolateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/281377/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.281379>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Collection localities of five Ctenus species. A. South America; B. Close up, northeastern South America. Legend: square = C. delesserti; black circle = C. falconensis and C. sigma; gray circle = C. nigritus; triangle = C. serratipes." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/281379/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

